## 📊 Observability

```python
# src/ai/observability.py

# ✅ Log per-query metrics
logger.info(
    "AI query completed",
    extra={
        "provider": "gemini",
        "model": "gemini-2.0-flash",
        "tokens_used": response.usage_metadata.total_token_count,
        "latency_ms": elapsed_ms,
        "estimated_cost": cost,
        "guardrail_triggered": False,
    }
)
```

### Rules
- Every AI call logs: provider, model, tokens, latency, cost, guardrail status
- AI logs go to dedicated `logs/ai.log` (separate from app logs)
- Cost estimation uses published API pricing (update when rates change)
- Surface metrics in Streamlit sidebar for transparency

